Interface CommonMethodOrConstructorDeclaration

All Superinterfaces:

All Known Subinterfaces:

public interface CommonMethodOrConstructorDeclaration
extends JSOM

This interface is the base type for all method or constructor declarations.

getGenericTypeParameters

java.util.List<GenericTypeParameter> getGenericTypeParameters()
Returns a list of generic type parameters that may have been stated left from the method's return type.

Example: public <T> T foo(T argument) {...}

For the example above this method would return a list that contains just one generic type parameter representing the type T stated by <T>.

Calling this method equals an getGenericTypeParameters(null) call.

Returns:
A list of generic type parameters. If there is no generic type parameter null will be returned.
See Also:
getGenericTypeParameters(List)

getGenericTypeParameters

java.util.List<GenericTypeParameter> getGenericTypeParameters(java.util.List<GenericTypeParameter> pList)
Returns a list of generic type parameters that may have been stated left from the method's return type.

Example: public <T> T foo(T argument) {...}

For the example above this method would return a list that contains just one generic type parameter representing the type T stated by <T>.

Parameters:
pList - If this argument isn't null the generic type parameters will be added to this list and this list object will be returned. Otherwise a new list will be created for the result.
Returns:
A list of generic type parameters. If there is no generic type parameter null will be returned, even if the argument pList isn't null.

removeFormalParameters

FormalParameterList removeFormalParameters()
Removes all formal parameter list.

If this has no formal parameters an implementation of this method is expected to do nothing than return null.

Returns:
